<subSubSection id="4CB96530B168FFA158FE9DBAFBA7F83F" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="041C36BBB168FFA158FE9DBAFE83F900" blockId="5.[189,310,1724,1750]" box="[189,310,1724,1750]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading id="5F5481D7B168FFA158FE9DBAFE83F900" bold="true" box="[189,310,1724,1750]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="3">
<emphasis id="36D7EAA9B168FFA158FE9DBAFE83F900" bold="true" box="[189,310,1724,1750]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="041C36BBB168FFA158FE9DEBFBA7F83F" blockId="5.[189,1399,1773,2025]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
A species morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C3A34D38B168FFA15AC29DEBFC89F8D1" box="[641,828,1773,1799]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manoelfelixii">
<emphasis id="36D7EAA9B168FFA15AC29DEBFC89F8D1" box="[641,828,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A. manoelfelixii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it has glabrous to glabrescent, lustrous vegetative parts and inflorescences. However, 
<taxonomicName id="C3A34D38B168FFA15AA19C15FCE0F8FA" authority="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix" authorityYear="2021" box="[738,853,1810,1837]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alatum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="36D7EAA9B168FFA15AA19C15FCE0F8FA" box="[738,853,1810,1837]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A. alatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2DE457D2B168FFA15B1D9C15FC0FF8FB" box="[862,954,1811,1837]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from this and other species of 
<taxonomicName id="C3A34D38B168FFA158FE9C3EFEDFF884" box="[189,362,1848,1874]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="36D7EAA9B168FFA158FE9C3EFEDFF884" box="[189,362,1848,1874]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ameroglossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by having conspicuous membranous wings on the stem extending to the peduncle of the inflorescence and the pedicel (vs not or sparsely winged). Because of its green stems and leaves, 
<taxonomicName id="C3A34D38B168FFA158FE9C82FE86F84B" authority="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,307,1923,1950]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alatum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="36D7EAA9B168FFA158FE9C82FE86F84B" box="[189,307,1923,1950]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A. alatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2DE457D2B168FFA1597C9C82FE2BF848" box="[319,414,1924,1950]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
may also appear similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C3A34D38B168FFA15AB89C82FCC0F84B" authority="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix" authorityYear="2021" box="[763,885,1923,1950]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bicolor" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="36D7EAA9B168FFA15AB89C82FCC0F84B" box="[763,885,1923,1950]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2DE457D2B168FFA15BC39C82FC57F848" box="[896,994,1924,1950]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, although it differs by having its inflorescence in a simple dichasium (vs compound dichasium), winged peduncles and pedicels (vs partially winged) and the sepals not overlapping (vs sepals overlapping).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4CB96530B16BFFA258FE9A0FFDC0FEAB" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="041C36BBB16BFFA258FE9A0FFEF1FEF5" blockId="6.[189,324,265,291]" box="[189,324,265,291]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading id="5F5481D7B16BFFA258FE9A0FFEF1FEF5" bold="true" box="[189,324,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis id="36D7EAA9B16BFFA258FE9A0FFEF1FEF5" bold="true" box="[189,324,265,291]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="041C36BBB16BFFA258FE9A3AFDC0FEAB" blockId="6.[189,1398,316,381]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
The name is derived from the Latin adjective ʻ 
<taxonomicName id="C3A34D38B16BFFA25AA29A3AFC9CFE80" authorityName="Barringer" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Cham. &amp; Schltdl." box="[737,809,316,342]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linderniaceae" genus="Cubitanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alatus">
<emphasis id="36D7EAA9B16BFFA25AA29A3AFC9CFE80" box="[737,809,316,342]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">alatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ʼ, ʻwingedʼ, referring to the conspicuous wings on the branches, peduncles and pedicels.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
